spans.text: Where the sharp rocks , in distant horror seen , Drive the white currents through the spreading green ; Where the loud Tiger , pawing in his rage , Bids the black Archers of the wilds engage
the black Archers of the wilds
the companion of his soul , Extended where loud Caigra's billows roll
of his soul , Extended where loud Caigra's billows roll
of warring Archers found , Where daily lightnings plough the sandy ground
the chase , Swifter than hunted Wolves they urge the race
'Twould drink a wider stream than Caigra's flood
the loud thunder of their arms
the sanguine sand The blasted of the lightnings of thy hand
the red fury of thy justice
of those bloody sons of mischief
What distant region holds thee from my arms
the gales , Majestic as the many coloured Snake
to Jaghirs shores ; Swift as the arrow , hasting to the breast , Was Cawna the companion of my rest
from the wood a prowling Tiger came
He fled , though wounded , to a distant waste , I urged the furious flight with fatal haste
The pallid shadows of the azure waves
The pallid shadows of the azure waves
my Cawna and my children slaves
my Heccar , have I cause for rage
I'll strew the beaches with the mighty dead And tinge the lily of their features red
